## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="a01ab-116">El ejemplo siguiente se controla el <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType>, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType>, o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType> eventos y la envía a la información de la consola sobre el audio reconocido que está asociado con el resultado de reconocimiento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a01ab-116">The following example handles the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType>, <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType>, or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar.SpeechRecognized?displayProperty=nameWithType> event and outputs to the console information about the recognized audio that is associated with the recognition result.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
// Handle the SpeechRecognized event.   
void SpeechRecognizedHandler(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs e)  
{  
  if (e.Result == null) return;  
  
  RecognitionResult result = e.Result;  
  
  Console.WriteLine("Grammar({0}): {1}",  
    result.Grammar.Name, result.Text);  
  
  if (e.Result.Audio != null)  
  {  
    RecognizedAudio audio = e.Result.Audio;  
  
    Console.WriteLine("   start time: {0}", audio.StartTime);  
    Console.WriteLine("   encoding format: {0}", audio.Format.EncodingFormat);  
    Console.WriteLine("   position: {0}, duration: {1}",  
      audio.AudioPosition, audio.Duration);  
  }  
  
  // Add event handler code here.  
}  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="a01ab-119">Esta propiedad hace referencia a la posición al principio de la frase reconocida en la secuencia de audio generado del dispositivo de entrada.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a01ab-119">This property references the position at the beginning of the recognized phrase in the input device's generated audio stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a01ab-120">Por el contrario, el `RecognizerAudioPosition` propiedad de la <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> y <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> hacen referencia a las clases de posición del reconocedor dentro de su entrada de audio.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a01ab-120">By contrast, the `RecognizerAudioPosition` property of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> classes reference the recognizer's position within its audio input.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a01ab-121">Estas posiciones pueden ser diferentes.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a01ab-121">These positions can be different.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a01ab-122">Para obtener más información, consulte [mediante eventos de reconocimiento de voz](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/01c598ca-2e0e-4e89-b303-cd1cef9e8482).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a01ab-122">For more information, see [Using Speech Recognition Events](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/01c598ca-2e0e-4e89-b303-cd1cef9e8482).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a01ab-123">El <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedAudio.StartTime%2A> propiedad obtiene la hora del sistema al principio de la operación de reconocimiento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a01ab-123">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedAudio.StartTime%2A> property gets the system time at the start of the recognition operation.</span></span>  
  
   
  
